description: More than seven weeks after the general election, Irish parties have still to form a new government.
title: Irish election: Green Party divided on coalition government
title_page: Irish election: Green Party divided on coalition government - BBC News
maintext: Others in the party have serious reservations about whether the Greens will be able to get their way on projects in government at time when budgets will be much tighter because of the economic response to Covid-19.
